ne 0.17, L-Isoleucine 0.24, L-Leucine 1, L-Methionine 0.125, L-Tyrosine 0.3, L-Valine 0.7; Vitamins Biotin 0.006,", "recipe_confidence": "high", "base_medium": "CDM35 (chemically defined medium, 35 components; final pH 7). Target medium CDMG = CDM35 base with glucose at 2% (20 g/L). CDMG agar plate additionally contains agar + an acidic chromogenic agent (pH indicator) used to detect acid production.", "base_medium_reference": "Ponomarova O., Gabrielli N., Sevin D.C., Mulleder M., Zirngibl K., Bulyha K., Andrejev S., Kafkia E., Typas A., Sauer U., Ralser M., Patil K.R. 'Yeast creates a niche for symbiotic lactic acid bacteria through nitrogen overflow.' Cell Systems 5(4):345-357.e6 (2017). DOI 10.1016/j.cels.2017.09.002; PMID 28964698; PMC5660601. Full CDM35 composition given in Supplemental Table S1 (mmc1). This is reference [49] ('Olga et al.') cited by the target paper."}, "components": [{"name": "L-arginine", "bigg_metabolite": "arg__L", "exchange": "EX_arg__L_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"reactome": "R-ALL-113530", "kegg": "C00062", "chebi": "CHEBI:13077", "kegg_drug": "D02982", "hmdb": "HMDB00517", "biocyc": "META:ARG", "mnx": "MNXM739527", "inchikey": "ODKSFYDXXFIFQN-BYPYZUCNSA-O", "seed": "cpd00051", "metacyc": "ARG", "sabiork": "23080", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C6H14N4O2/c7-4(5(11)12)2-1-3-10-6(8)9/h4H,1-3,7H2,(H,11,12)(H4,8,9,10)/p+1/t4-/m0/s1", "formula": "C6H15N4O2"}, "in_biggr": true, "exchange_source": "biggr", "mapping_method": "name_remap", "mapping_confidence": "inferred", "role": "amino acid/nitrogen"}, {"name": "L-asparagine", "bigg_metabolite": "asn__L", "exchange": "EX_asn__L_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"reactome": "R-ALL-29642", "kegg": "C00152", "chebi": "CHEBI:13083", "inchikey": "DCXYFEDJOCDNAF-REOHCLBHSA-N", "hmdb": "HMDB00168", "biocyc": "META:ASN", "mnx": "MNXM1107821", "seed": "cpd00132", "metacyc": "ASN", "sabiork": "72", "inchi": "I